practitioner.about:
Dr. Dina Shaban Mohammed is a  Specialist in the Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology at the Sharjah branch of Medcare Medical Centre. She obtained her MBBS  and MSc in Obstetrics and Gynaecology from the Zagazig University in Egypt. She further acquired a Post Graduate Diploma in Obstetrics Ultrasound from Sharjah University. She is a member of the Egyptian Medical Syndicate.

Dr.Dina served in various MOH Hospitals as a Specialist in Obstetrics and Gynaecology in Egypt. At this juncture, she managed low and high-risk pregnancies, deliveries, gynaecological diseases, post-partum period,  contraception and different vaginal infections. She then joined the fetal medicine unit, performing early scan growth scans, doppler and basic anomaly scans. She subsequently moved to the UAE, working for many years in the Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology at Al Qassimi Women’s & Children’s Hospital (AQWCH), Sharjah.

Dr. Mohammed is a skilled Obstetrician and Gynaecologist, having managed a gamut of high-risk pregnancies of patients with diabetes, hypertension and cardiac diseases. Besides carrying out normal deliveries, Caesarean section including end-stage Caesarean section, and ectopic pregnancies. She is proficient in both medical and surgical treatment of irregular uterine bleeding, infertility, miscarriage, endometrial hyperplasia, endometrial cervicitis and managing polycystic ovaries. She performs hysteroscopy and basic laparoscopy and is familiar with all methods of contraception, and doing obstetric and Doppler scans.  

During her leisure hours, Dr.Dina loves reading a good book as well as socializing with family and friends. She speaks Arabic, English and a smattering of Urdu.

locations.about:
Medcare Medical Centre (Medcare Sharjah) is a multispecialty medical center conveniently located at Al Jawhar Tower, opposite Sharjah Expo Center and beside the National Bank of Umm Al Quwain. Medcare Sharjah houses 14 doctors specialized in 11 expertises:  cardiology, dentistry, dermatology, ear nose and throat (ENT), family medicine, internal medicine, obstetrics & gynecology, ophthalmology, orthopedics, pediatrics, and rheumatology. 

With a reserved parking dedicated to patients, Medcare Sharjah welcomes people in need of diagnosis or treatment in a friendly environment. Medcare Sharjah is reputed for the friendly and attentive support that patients receive from its multilingual and empathic medical team. Considered as the UAE’s most preferred clinic, Medcare Sharjah is an ideal healthcare destination as it is fully equipped with a laboratory and diagnostic services along with an in-house pharmacy. 

Medcare Sharjah is part of 9 medical centers, 4 specialty centers, and 4 multispeciality hospitals, with over 350 highly qualified doctors in total.
